        'Prophylactic antibiotics make vaccines unnecessary in immunodeficient patients — FALSE: vaccines (killed/inactivated) provide antigen-specific immune priming where possible; prophylactic antibiotics provide broad-spectrum protection but do not generate immunological memory; both are complementary strategies, not alternatives'
